ICYMI: On February 3, 2020, we unveiled the solar panels on Clinton's roof with a ribbon-cutting ceremony. Here are some facts about the solar project:

- The solar panels will generate over 15% of the District's future energy consumption.

- Excess energy exported will offset energy consumption at other schools throughout the District.

- All existing electrical service was upgraded to accommodate the new system.

- The solar panels are arranged at a fixed 10-degree tilt to maximize energy performance on all open roof areas.

- An output display has ben mounted in the lobby of District Office to show real-time energy consumption.

- There is a guaranteed annual energy savings of $84,500

Check out the news article on our website (link below) for pictures from the ribbon-cutting ceremony!

http://www.comsewogue.k12.ny.us/district/news_information/what_s_new/clinton_solar_project_ribbon-_cutting_ceremony

The results are in!

The Budget has PASSED, with a vote of 829 to 263.

The Bond has PASSED, with a vote of 768 to 315.

Trustee Elections have been confirmed for John Swenning, Rick Rennard and Corey Prinz.

Thank You Comsewogue Community for voting and for all of your support. GO WARRIORS!
